<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1092" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1092">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4058.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s May 1. General Carranza has telegraphed urgent orders to
                            General Natera, Constitutionalist military commander in the State of
                            Zacatecas, regarding liberation of Emery should he be held by any of his
                            forces. Zacatecas is still held by Federals. Constitutionalist
                            authorities here are slow to believe that Emery is held by their
                            forces.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>